          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=660B6D5E-1625-4388-9BA2-82874CFBAE59&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Ftaiwan-amps-up-chinese-invasion-drills-to-deliver-a-message-war-could-happen-705e6343&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">在乌克兰战争和对中国大陆入侵的担忧日益加剧之后，台湾的年度军事演习和民用演习今年急剧扩大。 《华尔街日报》访问了这个民主岛屿，了解它准备如何保卫自己。照片：王乔宇<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001092728"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/joyu-wang" itemprop="url" rel="author">王乔宇</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 28 日上午 5:54（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/taiwan-amps-up-chinese-invasion-drills-to-deliver-a-message-war-could-happen-705e6343"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>台湾台南——俯瞰台湾海峡的这座城市的郊区，两栋住宅楼前爆炸，一栋摇摇欲坠地靠在另一栋上。消防队员冲向闷烧的残骸，扑灭大火，并开始疯狂搜寻幸存者。</p><p>附近的扩音器里响起一个女声，向围观的人群讲述这一场景。</p><p> “中国人的袭击导致一辆公共汽车翻倒，几栋建筑物倾斜倒塌，许多人被困，”该女子说。 “台南市遭受不分青红皂白的导弹袭击。”</p><p>这一场景和其他模拟混乱场景均以电影制作价值呈现，是周二在台湾南部城市进行的灾难应对演习的一部分，该演习与针对假想的中国入侵的多日军事演习同时进行。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="570" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825566?width=860&amp;height=570" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">周四，台湾一个主要港口附近举行了反登陆演习。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Joyu Wang/华尔街日报</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>演习和演习<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-concerns-about-taiwan-put-focus-on-islands-defensive-weakness-11619113253?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">每年都会举行</a>，并且总是带有戏剧性的元素，但今年的规模更大、声音更大、更加协调。与会者和政治分析人士表示，此举的目的是传达一个明确的信息：战争随时可能爆发。</p><p>台湾总统蔡英文过去一直对这种情绪持谨慎态度，担心播下可能削弱经济的恐慌情绪。但随着中国在台湾周边的军事活动加剧，以及乌克兰战争凸显了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russian-invasion-ukraine-battle-of-kyiv-ragtag-army-11663683336?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">做好充分准备的民众</a>的重要性，台北的算计已经开始发生转变。</p><p>北京的共产党领导人<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-taiwan-relations-tensions-explained-11653322751?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">认为台湾是中国的一部分</a>，并誓言要把这个自治岛屿置于自己的控制之下，必要时可以使用武力，尽管他们从未统治过台湾。中国领导人习近平将解决台湾问题视为其所谓的民族复兴中国梦的核心，并表示这是一项“不应该代代相传的任务”。</p><p>没有迹象表明军事对抗迫在眉睫，但近年来<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-threatens-retaliation-if-kevin-mccarthy-meets-taiwans-tsai-ing-wen-66e5e597?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，随着台北和华盛顿之间的关系日益紧张，将台湾与</a>中国分隔开的 100 英里宽的台湾海峡的紧张局势加剧。一些军事分析家警告说，数十年来一直生活在理论上的中国入侵威胁下的台湾民众并没有充分意识到冲突风险的增加。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="464" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825567?width=700&amp;height=464" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">模拟中国导弹袭击住宅楼的爆炸是周二在台湾台南市进行的灾难应对演习的一部分。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Joyu Wang/华尔街日报</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>台南的防灾演习通常以台风、地震等自然灾害为重点。今年，市政府官员首次将演习时间与年度军事和空袭演习同时进行，并练习应对战时情况。</p><p>在政府高级官员和高级军事官员与美国驻台北大使馆的特遣队一起观看的情况下，该市模拟了对建筑物的导弹袭击，火焰云射向天空，一枚肮脏的炸弹在民用机场爆炸。</p><p>警察队伍的任务是制服冒充居民并试图制造混乱的中国渗透者，而社区领导人则练习疏散居民和学童。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> “今天在台南举行的演习，包括模拟战时情景，不仅仅是因为俄罗斯乌克兰战争引发了国际敏感性的提高，”台湾行政院院长陈建仁周二在演习后表示。 “这更反映出中国对我国不断的威胁和挑衅。”</p><p>蔡英文在新冠病毒检测呈阳性后错过了周二的演习，但她周四驾驶悍马车出现在台湾西北海岸的海滩上，观看一场异常大型的反登陆演习，并参观了一条军事战壕，她说这个战壕的灵感来自于乌克兰的堑壕战。 。</p><p> “未来，我们面临的威胁和挑战将更加复杂。我们需要预测复合威胁场景，制定相关预案，加强训练演练。”她周四表示。</p><p>台湾淡江大学中国军事专家林英宇表示，反登陆演习在现代战争中的军事意义较小，但有助于传递一个象征性信息，即台湾有能力抵御中国军队。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824742?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">台湾总统蔡英文周四视察军事演习。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：ANN WANG/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>林说，“天助自助者”，这是台湾国防部试图向华盛顿领导人传达的信息，在与北京的任何军事对抗中，台北都需要华盛顿领导人的支持。 “我们不是一块容易被踢碎的豆腐。”</p><p>美国军事规划者<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/taiwan-military-readiness-china-threat-us-defense-11635174187?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">质疑台湾军队是否已做好</a>与中国大陆对抗的准备，理由是准备不足且士气低落。蔡政府<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/taiwan-to-extend-mandatory-military-service-11672129529?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">扩大了征兵规模并全面改革了训练</a>，以解决这些问题。</p><p>这是自去年夏天时任众议院议长<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/nancy-pelosi">南希·佩洛西</a>访问台北后，中国以军舰<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-boasts-of-ability-to-blockade-taiwan-as-military-exercises-continue-11659695158?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">模拟军事封锁</a>包围台湾以来的首次演习和演习。当时，一些西方政治分析人士猜测，北京的愤怒反应可能会让普通台湾民众意识到中国所构成的日益严重的威胁。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>未来五年台湾发生战争的可能性有多大？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>几个月后，效果似乎减弱了。国立政治大学选举研究中心3月份进行的一项调查显示，超过30%的受访者将中国入侵的可能性评为6或更高（从0到10），其中10代表入侵的确定性。这一比例略高于一年前的 28%。</p><p>由于预计周五将袭击该岛东南海岸的强台风，本周的几次演习不得不改变或取消，但演习规模的扩大和强度的增加至少给一些人留下了印象。</p><p>在台北的一次防空演习中，送货司机吴景荣不得不将摩托车停在地铁站地下30分钟。他说，他理解由于台湾海峡紧张局势加剧，有必要让公民做好应对紧急情况的准备。<br><br> “作为平民，我们能做的就是找到合适的地方藏身，”他说。 “剩下的就看政府了。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824743?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">台湾桃园国际机场的士兵本周参加模拟中国入侵的演习。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：布伦南·奥康纳/祖玛出版社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>今年的军事演习，正式名称为“汉光演习”，比以往更加关注对主要基础设施和交通枢纽（包括岛上最大机场）的威胁。</p><p>周三，前台湾特种部队士兵廖欧文与一位前军人朋友前往天文台，观看部队从四架黑鹰直升机上降落，模拟袭击台湾桃园国际机场。他驳回了有关机场首次参加演习导致航班延误的投诉。</p><p> “如果台湾不努力自力更生，没有人愿意帮助你，”他说。</p><p>写信给 Joyu Wang： <a href="mailto:joyu.wang@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">joyu.wang@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 09:54:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/taiwan-amps-up-chinese-invasion-drills-to-deliver-a-message-war-could-happen-705e6343</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/taiwan-amps-up-chinese-invasion-drills-to-deliver-a-message-war-could-happen-705e6343<author><![CDATA[Joyu Wang]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Israel’s Government Looks at Next Steps in Judicial Overhaul]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>在通过限制法院权力的法律后，联盟现在正在寻求改变法官的任命方式<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001092879"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825179?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">系着蓝色领带的以色列总理本杰明·内塔尼亚胡表示，他将给反对派在 11 月中旬之前达成妥协方案的时间。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：abir sultan/Shutterstock </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001092879"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dov-lieber" itemprop="url" rel="author">多夫·利伯</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 28 日上午 4:34 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/israels-government-looks-at-next-steps-in-judicial-overhaul-shrugging-off-protests-7172e0ad"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>特拉维夫——以色列总理本杰明·内塔尼亚胡的联盟<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/israel-netanyahu-government-judicial-overhaul-protests-862dffd3?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">本周取得了重大胜利</a>，通过了旨在重建该国司法机构的一揽子立法的第一部分。现在，它已准备好迎接更多。</p><p>最重要的是让民选官员<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-judge-at-the-heart-of-israels-constitutional-crisis-de698670?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">控制法官遴选委员会</a>，这是司法改革中最具争议的部分之一。内塔尼亚胡在三月份搁置了一项法案，该法案将让政府在面对<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-israels-citizen-soldiers-forced-netanyahu-to-retreat-on-judicial-overhaul-21d55e4e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">大规模抗议和预备役军人威胁的情况</a>下获得该委员会的多数控制权，如果该法案获得通过，则将停止报到。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netanyahu-faces-fresh-stand-off-with-israeli-reservists-over-judicial-overhaul-b974d3f5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">来自预备役军人的抗议和威胁</a>并没有阻止内塔尼亚胡推进该计划的第一部分，该计划于周一在没有反对派支持的情况下通过成为法律。内塔尼亚胡周四在接受美国广播公司新闻采访时表示，如果反对派不与政府妥协，他准备继续单方面通过司法改革。</p><p>内塔尼亚胡说：“现在他们看到我们已经准备好在没有他们的情况下采取行动——我们拥有多数——也许我们能够与他们一起采取行动。”他表示，他将给予反对派在 11 月中旬之前达成妥协方案的时间。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=B58B7540-4CF9-464C-A04F-C0E71926FD01&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fisraels-government-looks-at-next-steps-in-judicial-overhaul-shrugging-off-protests-7172e0ad&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">以色列医生周二举行罢工，当局在因总理本杰明·内塔尼亚胡政府进行的司法改革而发生骚乱的夜晚，强行将抗议者从道路上带走。照片：阿米尔·利维/盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>在两轮谈判失败后，以色列反对派领导人亚伊尔·拉皮德表示，他将拒绝参加不认真的谈判。 “反对派不会参与一场空洞的谈判，”他周一表示。</p><p>近30周以来，以色列人一直在抗议一项旨在限制最高法院权力并将更多控制权交给立法者的司法改革计划。周四晚上， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/israeli-protesters-pledge-to-intensify-civil-unrest-76b69af9?mod=world_lead_pos4&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">数万人走上街头抗议</a>政府重塑司法机构的努力。</p><p>该计划的支持者表示，为了控制自由派、激进的法院，这些改变是必要的，因为法院太容易推翻民选官员的意愿。反对者表示，该计划破坏了制衡制度，并将允许内塔尼亚胡的右翼、极端民族主义和宗教保守党派联盟通过法院通常认为违宪的立法。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825237?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">特拉维夫抗议司法改革的抗议者。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：阿米尔·科恩/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825232?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">以色列预备役军人在特拉维夫游行反对拟议的改革。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：祖玛出版社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>以色列议会 (Knesset) 将于 7 月 30 日进入夏季休会期，直到 10 月中旬才会返回，这意味着在任何立法重新进行辩论之前都将有一个暂停。</p><p>领导司法改革的议员之一西姆查·罗斯曼(Simcha Rothman)表示，该联盟希望继续改变法官的任命方式，并“以负责任的方式继续纠正司法系统”。他说他希望在与反对派合作的同时做到这一点。</p><p>司法任命委员会由九名成员组成，目前由现任法官、以色列律师协会成员、执政联盟代表以及传统上反对派成员组成。投票是分开的，因此没有一个团体在委员会中拥有多数发言权。</p><p>目前还没有提出新的法案，内塔尼亚胡和罗斯曼表示，他们将在未来几周内考虑如何修改立法。</p><p>但该法案的一个版本于二月份在议会提出，但于三月份被搁置， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/israel-protests-judicial-overhaul-netanyahu-7e264a71?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">该版本将改变司法遴选委员会</a>，以便执政联盟将被允许在不受反对的情况下任命其任期内的前两名最高法院法官。此后，最高法院的任命将需要一名反对派成员和一名法官的支持。最高法院院长也将由该委员会任命，而不是按照目前的资历任命，而且委员会中将不再有律师协会成员。</p><p>内塔尼亚胡<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netanyahu-revives-judicial-overhaul-stripped-of-most-controversial-piece-33160de?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">上个月在接受《华尔街日报》采访时表示</a>，他认为赋予立法者在委员会中的决定性发言权没有问题。</p><p> “目前持续存在的批评是，你不能让民选官员选择法官，因为那是民主的终结。那么，在这种情况下，美国就不是一个民主国家，”内塔尼亚胡说。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825211?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">反对党领袖亚伊尔·拉皮德表示，他将拒绝参加不认真的谈判。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：AMMAR AWAD/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>Amir Fuchs, a legal scholar with the Israel Democracy Institute, a Jerusalem-based think tank, said the current system for appointing judges is set up so that both the judges and politicians have a veto over each other. He said that there are conservative justices in line to join the committee.</p><p> “I think the system provides a really good and diverse Supreme Court, and in time it becomes more equal,” he said.</p><p> Israel&#39;s Justice Minister Yariv Levin, one of the architects of the government&#39;s plan, has refused to convene the committee to appoint judges until he can change its current makeup.</p><p> The Supreme Court is <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/israels-supreme-court-could-strike-down-a-bill-aimed-at-limiting-its-power-but-will-it-cc17a8d7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">slated in September to hear a petition</a> from the centrist Yesh Atid party, headed by Lapid, to demand the committee be convened to fill empty positions on the court. Some legal scholars say the committee cannot be changed after a recent vote passed to place two new lawmakers on the committee, one from the opposition and one from the coalition.</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> Aside from changing the way judges are appointed, the coalition has other legislation it hopes to pursue. This includes making the opinions of the attorney general and legal adviser to ministers advisory rather than binding as it currently stands. The coalition also wants to prevent the Supreme Court from being able to strike down Israel&#39;s quasi-constitutional laws, known as basic laws, and limit what cases the court can hear.</p><p> Netanyahu told the Journal that he wasn&#39;t going to pursue a bill that would allow the Knesset to override Supreme Court decisions with a simple majority of lawmakers. Some in his coalition have since said Netanyahu told them he would bring the bill back but in a different form.</p><p> Abraham Diskin, a political scientist with the Kohelet Forum, a Jerusalem-based think tank that helped craft the government legislation, said that right-wing governments that have been in power since the late 1970s have never been able to fully carry out their vision because the Supreme Court has repeatedly struck down major legislative priorities.</p><p> “De facto, the real decisions on all issues was out of their hands,” he said. “The court is the single and most powerful of all factors in policy and decision making.”</p><p>写信给 Dov Lieber，邮箱为<a href="mailto:dov.lieber@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">dov.lieber@wsj.com</a></p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Ari Flanzraich contributed to this article.</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 08:34:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/israels-government-looks-at-next-steps-in-judicial-overhaul-shrugging-off-protests-7172e0ad</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/israels-government-looks-at-next-steps-in-judicial-overhaul-shrugging-off-protests-7172e0ad<author><![CDATA[Dov Lieber]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>本杰明·内塔尼亚胡</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[North Korea Celebrates Major Holiday With Special Guests From China and Russia]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>平壤举行大型阅兵，自疫情以来首次允许外国代表团入境<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001089231"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=901F4C0B-AEB7-4EE0-90AB-3AAD0B945CAA&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fnorth-korea-celebrates-major-holiday-with-special-guests-from-china-and-russia-fc3386fc&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">朝鲜媒体显示，领导人金正恩带着俄罗斯国防部长谢尔盖·绍伊古参观了一个装满武器的大厅，包括导弹和无人机。此次活动正值俄罗斯和中国代表团访问朝鲜，庆祝朝鲜战争结束 70 周年。照片：法新社/朝中社/KNS<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001089231"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dasl-yoon" itemprop="url" rel="author">达斯尔·尹</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 27 日晚上 10:24（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-korea-celebrates-major-holiday-with-special-guests-from-china-and-russia-fc3386fc"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>首尔——朝鲜欢迎中国和俄罗斯高级官员来庆祝朝鲜战争武装冲突结束周年纪念日，这是面对美国在该地区军事存在不断增加，这三个国家加强关系的最新表现。</p><p>星期四是结束朝鲜战争三年战斗的停战协议 70 周年。据官方媒体报道，朝鲜举行了晚间阅兵，朝鲜在平壤市中心举行了晚间阅兵，展示了其最新的洲际弹道导弹（Hwasong-18）以及其他新进展。</p><p>作为庆祝活动的一部分， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-korea-kim-jong-un-family-succession-11612436917?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">朝鲜 39 岁的独裁者</a>金正恩本周接待了由俄罗斯国防部长谢尔盖·绍伊古和中国政治局委员李鸿忠率领的代表团。三人均参加了阅兵式。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>自 Covid-19 大流行开始以来，朝鲜已封锁其边界。自那时起，唯一正式允许进入该国的外国人是今年早些时候来到平壤的新任中国驻平壤大使。即使是朝鲜国民，例如俄罗斯和中国的劳工，也因担心大流行而被阻止进入自己的祖国。</p><p>面对美国在该地区日益增加的军事存在，平壤找到了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-war-gives-north-korea-reasons-to-draw-closer-to-russia-11661695201?mod=Searchresults_pos1&amp;page=1&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">深化与北京和莫斯科结盟的</a>机会，以获得急需的经济生命线，并免受国际社会对其非法武器试验的惩罚。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824651?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">朝鲜领导人金正恩、俄罗斯国防部长谢尔盖·绍伊古和中国政治局委员李鸿忠在平壤观看演出。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：朝中社/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>朝鲜问题专家安东尼·林纳 (Anthony Rinna) 表示，通过邀请俄罗斯和中国官员参加周四的阅兵，朝鲜可以发出这样的信息：两国默许<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-korea-passes-law-allowing-pre-emptive-nuclear-strikes-11662709820?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">平壤自行宣布的核地位</a>，并给人一种该政权拥有强大支持者的感觉。中国-朝鲜研究小组的俄罗斯与朝鲜关系，这是一个专注于中国和朝鲜的网站。</p><p> “平壤可能希望强化这三个国家都站起来对抗西方的说法，”林纳说。</p><p>中国、俄罗斯和朝鲜日益相互支持，各自加剧与美国及其盟友的对抗。据国家通讯社塔斯社报道，继<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/vladimir-putin">习近平</a><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-xi-jinping-vladimir-putin-meet-in-russia-400d39e1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">三月访问莫斯科</a>后，俄罗斯总统弗拉基米尔·普京计划于十月访问中国，讨论经济合作。美国<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-korea-sending-artillery-to-russia-for-war-in-ukraine-white-house-says-11667403537?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">指责朝鲜</a>向俄罗斯提供乌克兰战争军事援助，莫斯科和平壤对此予以否认。中国与朝鲜的跨境贸易再次接近疫情前的水平。在上个月发出的一封信中，金正恩赞扬习近平加强了中国的国家实力和国际地位。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824654?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">朝鲜领导人在武器展览会上接待了俄罗斯总统绍伊古。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：朝中社/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>尽管朝鲜自去年以来发射了 100 多枚弹道导弹，但中国和俄罗斯<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-stymies-once-united-u-n-panel-on-north-korea-sanctions-11631714247?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">阻止了美国主导的联合国安理会追加制裁行动</a>。在联合国安理会会议上，北京和莫斯科将朝鲜的军力建设归咎于华盛顿对平壤的“敌对”政策以及美国与东京和首尔日益增强的军事联盟。</p><p>美国国务院发言人本周早些时候表示，北京和莫斯科可以利用其影响力鼓励平壤不要采取威胁性的非法行为。</p><p> 1953 年 7 月 27 日，以美国为首的联合国军司令部、朝鲜和中国签署停战协定，结束了朝鲜战争中的军事敌对行动。和平条约尚未签署，这意味着朝鲜和南方在技术上仍处于战争状态。</p><p>在平壤的历史记载中，该国抵御了美军的入侵，并将 7 月 27 日庆祝为“胜利日”。但美国和韩国的历史记录显示，朝鲜领导人金日成发起了对韩国的攻击。战争期间，中国军队在苏联空军的援助下支持朝鲜。</p><p>韩国并不认为7月27日是假期，而是将其称为停战纪念日。周四，韩国总统尹锡烈邀请数十名外国退伍军人纪念 1950 年至 1953 年冲突中阵亡的士兵。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>西方是否应该担心俄罗斯、中国和朝鲜之间关系的深化？为什么或者为什么不？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>过去一年里，尹政府<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-nuclear-capable-boomer-sub-visits-south-korea-for-first-time-in-decades-dc4a8187?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">寻求美国做出更强有力的保证</a>，保证在金氏政权遭受核攻击时将使用核武器保护首尔。尹是一位保守派人士， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-koreas-provocations-push-tensions-with-the-south-to-highest-in-years-11665748167?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">支持对平壤采取更具对抗性的立场</a>，他还实现了韩国与日本的关系正常化，加强了对朝鲜不断升级的核进展的三边威慑。</p><p>周三，金正恩在武器展上接待了俄罗斯总统绍伊古，展示了新型军用无人机和洲际弹道导弹。据平壤官方媒体报道，金正恩向绍伊古通报了扩大军事能力的计划，两人沿着安装在导弹发射车上的一排导弹行走。金正恩还向在“反美斗争”中牺牲的中国军人表示敬意。</p><p>哈德逊研究所亚太安全主席帕特里克·克罗宁表示，俄罗斯国防部长的出席“展示了俄罗斯与朝鲜在乌克兰战争期间进行防务合作的想法，以及抵御美国及其盟友的必要性”。华盛顿的智囊团。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824134?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">金正恩还向在战争中牺牲的中国军人表示敬意。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：朝中社/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>据朝鲜官方媒体报道，金正恩周三还会见了中国代表团，李克强在会上转交了习近平的一封信，但该媒体没有详细说明信函的内容。金正恩表示，这次访问体现了习近平“高度重视”两国关系的意愿。</p><p> 2023年上半年<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-korea-receives-aid-from-china-as-covid-outbreak-spreads-11652863549?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，北京和平壤之间的贸易额</a>已反弹至接近疫情前水平，比去年同期增长了两倍。上周，七国集团和一些欧洲国家在致中国的一封信中对多艘油轮的存在表示担忧，这些油轮为朝鲜受制裁的石油产品贸易提供了便利。</p><p>华盛顿智库布鲁金斯学会的中国问题专家帕特里夏·M·金(Patricia M. Kim)表示，近年来，平壤<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-tries-to-reassure-u-s-amid-speculation-around-missing-foreign-minister-82697971?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在北京和华盛顿之间的分歧</a>中感受到了为其经济和武器计划争取更多支持的机会。</p><p>金正恩表示：“中国和朝鲜今天有一个共同观点，即美国在该地区的存在及其与韩国和日本的联盟网络正在削弱他们的战略利益。”</p><p>写信给 Dasl Yoon，邮箱为<a href="mailto:dasl.yoon@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">dasl.yoon@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 02:24:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-korea-celebrates-major-holiday-with-special-guests-from-china-and-Russia-fc3386fc</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-korea-celebrates-major-holiday-with-special-guests-from-china-and-Russia-fc3386fc<author><![CDATA[Dasl Yoon]]></author><category>华尔街日报</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>贸易/外部支付</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国际制裁</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>贸易壁垒/限制</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>金正恩</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>贸易</category><category>外部支付</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国际制裁</category><category>政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>贸易壁垒</category><category>限制</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Replaced, Then Erased: Mystery Deepens Around China’s Former Foreign Minister]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>外交部网站上几乎所有提及秦刚担任部长的内容都被删除，加剧了猜测<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001085354"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=9F7AF9B6-88BC-4AB6-B4C8-E0CF0C68E116&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Freplaced-then-erased-mystery-deepens-around-chinas-former-foreign-minister-9117007a&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">北京在周二的紧急会议上重新任命最高外交官王毅接替秦刚担任外交部长，但没有提及秦刚神秘缺席的问题。中国领导人习近平七个月前亲自挑选了秦国。照片：Florence Lo/Pool 路透社/美联社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001085354"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/wenxin-fan" itemprop="url" rel="author">范文欣</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 27 日晚上 9:52（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/replaced-then-erased-mystery-deepens-around-chinas-former-foreign-minister-9117007a"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> HONG KONG—China&#39;s former foreign minister, who was replaced on Tuesday after he went missing from public view for more than a month, is now disappearing from parts of the Foreign Ministry&#39;s website—an erasure that is intensifying intrigue around what happened to him.</p><p> Authorities didn&#39;t provide a reason for their <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-foreign-minister-qin-gang-replaced-63660fad?mod=world_lead_pos5&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">decision to remove</a> Qin Gang from his post, which has now been filled—at least temporarily—by his predecessor Wang Yi. The Foreign Ministry previously cited <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-tries-to-reassure-u-s-amid-speculation-around-missing-foreign-minister-82697971?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">unspecified health reasons</a> for Qin&#39;s absence.</p><p> Since replacing him with Wang, the ministry has scrubbed nearly all mentions of Qin as the foreign minister from its official website.同样，在流行的社交媒体平台<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/WB" class="">微博</a>上<span class="company-name-type">，</span>有关秦最近担任职务的许多内容也从该部门的微博账户中消失了。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>在毛泽东时代，众所周知，共产党会从照片和其他官方记录中删除高级官员，通常是在他们失宠并被清洗之后。此后的几十年里，这种高水平的擦除非常罕见，而且可能从未如此引人注目地进行过。</p><p> The changes attracted attention on <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/WB" class="company-name">Weibo</a> and in other corners of the Chinese internet, fueling fevered speculation about Qin&#39;s fate.</p><p> “Had Qin Gang not ever been a foreign minister?” one Chinese lawyer wrote in a post on Weibo. “The way the website handled this isn&#39;t appropriate.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823935?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">五月份在北京上映的《秦刚》已经从公众视野中消失一个多月了。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：托马斯·彼得/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>这位 57 岁的老人在担任中国领导人习近平精心挑选的外交部长不到七个月后，在外交队伍中<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-promotes-u-s-ambassador-to-foreign-minister-11672409545?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">的晋升速度异常迅速</a>。 Qin&#39;s online erasure undermined the notion that he was replaced as a result of serious health issues, political analysts said.</p><p> “即使健康问题导致秦先生被免去外交部长职务，但这也没有理由导致他在外交部网站上过去的会议记录被删除，” <a href="https://chinamediaproject.org/2023/07/26/chinas-foreign-minister-is-removed-and-erased/" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">美国</a>媒体中国项目主任戴维·班志远（David Bandurski）写道。 <a href="https://chinamediaproject.org/2023/07/26/chinas-foreign-minister-is-removed-and-erased/" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">基础研究小组</a>。</p><p> Asked about the changes at a regular press briefing on Wednesday, Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Mao Ning said the website was being updated according to protocols.</p><p>在发布会上，毛泽东被记者连珠炮般地询问秦的状况，她说她没有新的信息可提供。外交部网站上发布的新闻发布会记录中，所有记者提出的关于秦和毛泽东回应的问题都被省略了。</p><p>围绕秦的戏剧性事件发生在北京和华盛顿的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-and-china-see-fragile-opportunity-to-repair-ties-8ad7ddff?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">微妙时刻</a>，因为两国最近在紧张局势加剧之际才重新建立了高层沟通。 Political analysts say the 69-year-old Wang, the Communist Party&#39;s top foreign-affairs specialist, was likely installed as an interim replacement to buy time for Xi and other senior officials to find a more permanent solution.</p><p>美国国务卿安东尼·布林肯，</p>在访问太平洋岛国汤加时，他表示祝愿秦国一切顺利，并承诺与王毅合作，他已与王毅多次会面。<p></p><p> “I&#39;ve also known Wang Yi for more than a decade,” Blinken said. “I anticipate being able to work well with him, as we have in the past.”</p><p>政治分析人士表示，从长远来看，秦的接替不太可能破坏中美之间的外交，因为习近平制定了外交政策，尽管这凸显了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-locks-information-on-the-country-inside-a-black-box-9c039928?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国政治体系日益不透明</a>。</p><p> Searches on the Foreign Ministry website for Qin&#39;s name in Chinese or English returned no results on Wednesday. Qin continued to be listed as foreign minister in one statement on the site, which described him as representing China in the establishment of diplomatic ties in Honduras in March. Unlike the hundreds of other statements that have been removed, his name didn&#39;t appear in the headline on the Honduras item. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824129?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 6 月 18 日，国务卿安东尼·布林肯在北京会见了时任外交部长秦刚，几天前他最后一次公开露面。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：利亚·米利斯/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>通过流行应用程序上的外交部官方账户搜索秦的名字</p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TCEHY" class="company-name">微信</a>仍然产生了他担任外交部长期间的成果。 News items describing Qin in his previous roles as vice minister and ambassador to the US remain on the ministry&#39;s website.<p></p><p> State media accounts of Qin&#39;s removal haven&#39;t mentioned any change to his role as a state councilor, a senior government ranking in China&#39;s cabinet. As of Wednesday afternoon, the cabinet&#39;s website had been updated to remove mention of his ministerial role but continued to list his other titles, including as a member of the Communist Party&#39;s elite Central Committee.</p><p> China&#39;s internet censors have taken a selective approach to Qin. On Wednesday, Weibo was hiding search results under some hashtags related to his removal, as well as under a hashtag for “The Search for Qin,” a fantasy TV series set in China&#39;s ancient Qin dynasty.</p><p> But users otherwise were given space to continue indulging in speculation about the reasons for his disappearance, including the possibility of an extramarital affair.</p><p> “This is certainly not a normal job transfer,” wrote one Weibo user, nodding to the seeming ubiquity of the affair rumor on Chinese social media. The post received more than 10,000 likes.</p><p> Write to Wenxin Fan at <a href="mailto:wenxin.fan@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">wenxin.fan@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/bf4d14ac-311a-4b61-9cc1-ce0772d8de02.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 01:52:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/replaced-then-erased-mystery-deepens-around-chinas-former-foreign-minister-9117007a</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/replaced-then-erased-mystery-deepens-around-chinas-former-foreign-minister-9117007a<author><![CDATA[Wenxin Fan]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>微博</category><category>世界银行</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[New Trump Indictment Says He Ordered Mar-a-Lago Camera Footage Deleted]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Indictment also charges Carlos de Oliveira, a maintenance worker at Trump&#39;s Mar-a-Lago resort <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001090285"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=622E579A-90B4-48B4-890E-4E5CEFE7449F&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fdonald-trump-lawyers-jack-smith-jan-6-58c2fd14&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Former President Donald Trump faced new charges in his classified documents case on Thursday, according to special counsel Jack Smith&#39;s office. The new charges also included a new defendant.照片：杰拉尔德·赫伯特/美联社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001090285"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sadie-gurman" itemprop="url" rel="author">Sadie Gurman</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jan-wolfe" itemprop="url" rel="author">Jan Wolfe</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Updated July 27, 2023 8:35 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-lawyers-jack-smith-jan-6-58c2fd14"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> WASHINGTON— <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/donald-trump">Donald Trump</a> and his aides sought to have surveillance footage from his Mar-a-Lago club deleted so it couldn&#39;t be turned over to a grand jury, special counsel <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-lawyers-jack-smith-jan-6-58c2fd14#phrase-person?ref=PERSON%7CSmith%2C%20Jack;onlineSignificance=passing-mention" class="icon none">Jack Smith</a> alleged Thursday in new charges related to the former president&#39;s retention of classified documents after he left the White House.</p><p> The new indictment also charges Carlos de Oliveira, a maintenance worker at Trump&#39;s South Florida resort, making him the third defendant in the case.</p><p> The additional charges broaden an indictment brought by a Florida grand jury in June alleging the former president <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-indicted-in-document-case-b4e563d7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">held on to sensitive military secrets</a> he knew he shouldn&#39;t have retained access to, shared them with others and directed his staff to help him evade authorities&#39; efforts to get them back. And they come as Trump braces for separate federal charges over efforts to undo his 2020 election loss.</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> “This is nothing more than a continued desperate and failing attempt” by the Justice Department to “harass President Trump and those around him,” Trump spokesman Steven Cheung said, adding Smith was “casting about for any way to salvage their illegal witch hunt.”</p><p> The stepped-up charges heighten the extraordinary legal peril facing Trump as he campaigns for the nomination to win back the White House in 2024. The political risk is less clear, as the former president has only seemed to grow stronger among Republicans with each prosecution.</p><p> The original June indictment in the documents case charged Trump with 37 counts on <a href="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/documents/U.S.-Trump-Nauta-Indictment-6-8-2023.pdf" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">seven different charges</a> , including willful retention of national-defense information, withholding a record, false statements and conspiracy to obstruct.</p><p> On five of the counts, Trump was charged alongside his personal aide, Walt Nauta, who also faces a false-statements charge. Both he and Trump have pleaded not guilty to those charges. An attorney for de Oliveira, who was also charged with lying to investigators, didn&#39;t immediately respond to a request for comment. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824979?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Special counsel Jack Smith, center, is conducting a wide-ranging probe into attempts to undermine the 2020 election.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Mandel Ngan/Agence France-Presse/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> The superseding indictment returned Thursday charges Trump with an additional count of willful retention of national-defense information, stemming from a classified national-security document prosecutors said he showed to visitors at his golf club in New Jersey.</p><p> The indictment also charges both Trump and Nauta with two more counts of obstruction, counts which say that they and de Oliveira attempted to “alter, destroy, mutilate and conceal” evidence and that they tried to persuade someone else to do so when they pressured another employee to delete the footage.</p><p> According to the indictment, Trump had a 24-minute phone call with de Oliveira on June 23, 2022, the day after a lawyer for the Trump Organization received a draft grand-jury subpoena requiring the production of Mar-a-Lago security-camera footage.</p><p> A few days later, de Oliveira confronted the unnamed Mar-a-Lago staffer, identified in the indictment as the director of information technology at the resort, and told him that “the boss” wanted the footage deleted and, according to the indictment, asked “What are we going to do?”</p><p> The IT director told de Oliveira that he didn&#39;t know how to delete the server and that he didn&#39;t think he had the right to do that, according to the indictment, which doesn&#39;t say any of the footage was actually deleted.</p><p> Surveillance footage is at the heart of the Mar-a-Lago case, with prosecutors saying it shows Nauta moving dozens of boxes in the days before Justice Department investigators visited the property in June 2022 to retrieve records.</p><p> Prosecutors have alleged the footage showed Nauta moving 64 boxes out of the storage room for Trump to examine and later returning only about 30 of them. It was among the evidence the Justice Department used to justify its unprecedented <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-indicted-in-document-case-b4e563d7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">search of the former president&#39;s residence</a> two months later in August.</p><p> De Oliveira later lied to Federal Bureau of Investigation agents during a Jan. 13 interview at his home, according to the indictment, which said he had “personally observed and helped move Trump&#39;s boxes when they arrived at The Mar-a-Lago Club in January 2021,” but during his interview said he “never saw anything.”</p><p> The FBI agents had advised him that it was a voluntary interview, and that it is a crime to lie to the FBI, according to the indictment. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=AD509B15-E7B1-40F2-A20E-F0C3D878AE0B&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fdonald-trump-lawyers-jack-smith-jan-6-58c2fd14&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Former President Donald Trump said federal prosecutors told him he is a target of their investigation into efforts to undo his loss in the 2020 election, a sign he is likely to be indicted.照片：查理·尼伯格/美联社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>The new willful-retention charge relates to a document about a secret attack plan on a country that isn&#39;t named, but is identifiable as Iran. Prosecutors have said Trump in July 2021 bragged to a writer, publisher and two staff members at his golf club in Bedminster, NJ, about having the document, in audiotaped recordings now at the heart of the government&#39;s case.</p><p> “Isn&#39;t that amazing?” Trump told the group, adding: “Except it is, like, highly confidential.” He told them he could have declassified it as president, but couldn&#39;t anymore. “This is still a secret,” Trump said.</p><p> A federal judge has scheduled the trial in that case to begin on May 20, 2024.</p><p> Smith&#39;s office announced the new indictment just hours after Trump&#39;s lawyers met with prosecutors to try to head off additional criminal charges related to Trump&#39;s attempts to stay in power after President Biden&#39;s election win in November 2020, culminating in the Jan. 6, 2021, attack on the US Capitol.</p><p> The new indictment and the meeting kept the Justice Department as the focus of political interest, a day after a planned plea agreement on tax and gun charges for Biden&#39;s son, Hunter, collapsed during a <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-plea-deal-in-jeopardy-ff556d70?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">court hearing</a> where prosecutors surprised the defense team by saying they were still investigating him and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-plea-deal-limbo-republicans-749b5187?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">he could face new charges</a> .</p><p> Trump&#39;s schedule as he campaigns for the nomination to again run against Biden, a Democrat, could be complicated as court hearings mount, and the legal issues could play out differently in a general election.</p><p> Trump&#39;s campaign was ready for an indictment, complete with fundraising email blasts, and remains so. The former president has harnessed his legal problems into a broad argument of being politically targeted, with many Republican voters and lawmakers rallying around him.</p><p> Defense lawyers often use meetings such as the one Thursday morning to make last-ditch arguments against charging a client, but it couldn&#39;t immediately be determined what was discussed after Trump&#39;s lawyers John Lauro and Todd Blanche arrived at Smith&#39;s office, several miles from the Justice Department&#39;s main headquarters in downtown Washington. Prosecutors revealed little about their plans, as defense attorneys made their arguments against any charges, people familiar with the matter said.</p><p> A spokesman for Smith declined to comment.</p><p> Trump confirmed the meeting on his Truth Social platform. “My attorneys had a productive meeting with the DOJ this morning, explaining in detail that I did nothing wrong, was advised by many lawyers, and that an Indictment of me would only further destroy our Country,” he said. “会议期间没有发出通知的迹象。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825417?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> The indictment returned Thursday charges both former President Donald Trump and his personal aide, Walt Nauta, with two additional counts of obstruction.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Alon Skuy/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Prosecutors earlier this month told Trump&#39;s legal team <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-jack-smith-jan-6-letter-classified-documents-hearing-e679b87?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">he is a target</a> of Smith&#39;s far-ranging investigation into attempts by the former president and his allies to undermine the 2020 election.</p><p> The special counsel&#39;s target letter cites three statutes, according to a person familiar with the matter, including a Reconstruction-era civil-rights charge; conspiracy to defraud the US and obstruction of an official proceeding.</p><p> <em>—Alex Leary contributed to this article.</em></p><p> Write to Sadie Gurman at <a href="mailto:sadie.gurman@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">sadie.gurman@wsj.com</a> and Jan Wolfe at <a href="mailto:jan.wolfe@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jan.wolfe@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/a12c152d-cc1a-4b9e-a744-8a0d292d80a8.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 00:35:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-lawyers-jack-smith-jan-6-58c2fd14</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-lawyers-jack-smith-jan-6-58c2fd14<author><![CDATA[Sadie GurmanJan Wolfe]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Donald Trump</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.S. Economic Growth Accelerates]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>上季度经济增长2.4%，表明美国正在摆脱衰退<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001087898"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="581" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824191?width=860&amp;height=581" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">消费者支出一直在推动美国经济。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：贾斯汀·沙利文/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001087898"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sarah-chaney-cambon" itemprop="url" rel="author">莎拉·钱尼·坎本</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/christian-robles" itemprop="url" rel="author">克里斯蒂安·罗伯斯</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 27 日下午 5:20（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-gdp-report-economic-growth-92482437"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>尽管美联储<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/federal-reserve-raises-interest-rates-to-22-year-high-3c3e499c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">将利率推</a>至二十年来的高位，但今年春季更快的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/livecoverage/stock-market-today-dow-jones-07-27-2023?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">经济增长</a>提高了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/could-a-recession-still-be-years-away-soft-landing-could-deliver-another-extended-economic-cycle-e7e2c4ee?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">疫情后经济扩张时间更长</a>的前景。</p><p>美国商务部周四表示，经季节性因素和通胀因素调整后，第二季度<a href="https://www.bea.gov/sites/default/files/2023-07/gdp2q23_adv.pdf" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">国内</a>生产总值年增长率为 2.4%。这比经济学家预期的要快，并且高于今年前三个月 2% 的增长率。</p><p>第二季度消费者支出降温，但增长足以推动整体增长，同时商业投资也大幅增强。这些因素结合在一起，违背了经济学家此前的预期，即由于利率上升，经济衰退将在今年年中开始。</p><p>随着<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/consumer-price-index-report-june-inflation-ede7f4b1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">通胀从历史高位回落</a>且劳动力市场依然强劲，稳健的增长增加了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/as-inflation-goes-down-soft-landing-odds-improve-5166e6af?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">软着陆</a>的前景——即通胀在不出现衰退的情况下恢复到接近<a href="https://www.wsj.com/video/series/news-explainers/the-feds-2-inflation-target-explained/F0A8BD11-B153-4E7E-8454-B5C1C8CD12BD?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">美联储 2% 的目标</a>。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="850" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825207?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> AC Cutts &amp; Associates 首席经济学家艾米·克鲁斯·卡茨 (Amy Crews Cutts) 在数据发布前表示：“我们已经扭转了这里的风险，不再过度关注衰退，而是在衰退与非衰退之间保持平衡。”</p><p>美国股指周四走低。道琼斯工业平均指数下跌 237.40 点，跌幅 0.67%。更广泛的标准普尔 500 指数下跌 0.64%，以科技股为主的纳斯达克指数下跌 0.55%。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>美联储周三将基准利率上调0.25个百分点，至5.25%至5.5%之间，创22年来新高。美联储主席杰罗姆·鲍威尔表示，是否进一步加息将取决于通胀和经济活动放缓是否符合官员的预测。</p><p>他在新闻发布会上表示：“我们必须做好跟踪数据的准备，考虑到我们已经取得的进展，我们可以在事情展开时保持一点耐心和决心。”</p><p>继 2022 年初出现温和收缩后，过去一年经济增长速度超过 2%。经济增长与疫情爆发前十年的增速大致一致。</p><h3>消费者支出降温，仍推动增长</h3><p>第二季度消费者支出年增长率为1.6%，低于第一季度的4.2%。家庭支出占经济活动的大部分，占GDP增长总量的近一半。</p><p>经济放缓主要反映了美国人在今年年初抢购汽车后大件商品的购买降温，因为这些汽车又流回了经销店。</p><p> Visa 首席财务官 Vasant Prabhu 周二表示，近几个月消费者支出下降也反映出汽油价格下降。根据能源数据提供商 OPIS 的数据，每加仑普通汽油的平均价格比去年同期下降了约 60 美分。普拉布表示，除此之外，支出基本保持一致。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=6B575582-5695-4577-8048-E886C31EFE0B&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fus-gdp-report-economic-growth-92482437&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">美联储主席杰罗姆·鲍威尔周三表示，央行将把基准利率提高四分之一个百分点，使美国利率升至22年来的最高点。照片：内森·霍华德/美联社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>他表示，“自三月份以来，从富裕到低消费的消费者支出保持稳定”。 “我们的数据没有表明消费者群体的行为发生任何变化。”</p><p>美国人正受益于强劲的劳动力市场，工资涨幅<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/pay-raises-are-finally-beating-inflation-after-two-years-of-falling-behind-3e89bc2d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">最近超过了降温的通胀</a>。美国劳工部周四表示，作为裁员指标的初请失业金人数上周减少了 7,000 人，至经季节性调整后的 221,000 人。这是历史最低水平，基本上与 2019 年劳动力市场也强劲时的平均水平相符。</p><p>格斯·阿亚拉，</p>一位 73 岁的退休银行家正在挥霍一些大笔采购，同时减少一些日常用品的购买。这位亚利桑那州埃尔米拉日市的居民计划在今年晚些时候购买一辆混合动力汽车，并且可能会为这辆车提供融资，而不是支付现金。他和妻子的储蓄缓冲正在帮助支付妻子即将前往冰岛的旅行费用。<p></p><p> “我们想把钱花在对我们有利、让我们享受生活的事情上，”阿亚拉说。</p><p>阿亚拉改变了一些消费习惯以应对通货膨胀加剧。今年早些时候，他喜欢的一袋 12 盎司咖啡品牌的价格从去年的 9 美元飙升至 12 美元，今年早些时候，他转而购买更便宜的咖啡品牌 Seattle&#39;s Best。阿亚拉仍然需要每天喝咖啡，他一边喝着早晨的咖啡一边说道。</p><h3>今年春天商业投资猛增</h3><p>第二季度商业投资年率增长7.7%，较一季度的0.6%大幅增长。</p><p>尽管利率上升，但一些长期力量正在帮助刺激投资。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/americas-factory-building-boom-93dfb8f5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">联邦政府在芯片制造工厂和电动汽车工厂方面的支出激增</a>，抵消了其他一些削减。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="1300" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824784?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>第二季度企业设备支出出现反弹，这主要是由于供应链陷入混乱而对飞机和汽车的投资。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/RF" class="">Regions Financial</a>首席经济学家理查德·穆迪 (Richard F. Moody) 在一份报告中表示<span class="company-name-type">，</span>随着这一过程的结束，设备和机械支出可能会再次减弱。</p><p>第二季度净贸易增长略有下降，反映出<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-economy-barely-grows-as-recovery-fades-5652a92a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">全球经济低迷</a>。住宅投资连续第九个季度下降。最近住宅投资的下降反映出抵押贷款利率上升导致房地产市场紧张。</p><p>尽管如此，二手房长期短缺仍有助于支持新建筑。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/housings-recession-already-happened-26bbb505?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">房地产市场低迷</a>最严重的时期可能已经过去，这意味着未来几个月住宅投资可能会增长。</p><h3>对经济放缓的担忧依然存在</h3><p>今年晚些时候消费者和企业的支出是否会保持同样的速度尚不清楚。</p><p>高利率将持续存在，导致车辆、电器、工厂机器和建筑项目的借贷成本更高。此外，学生贷款偿还将于今年晚些时候恢复，这对一些消费者来说是另一个阻力。</p><p> Ben &amp; Jerry&#39;s 冰淇淋、Hellmann&#39;s 蛋黄酱和 Dove 肥皂的制造商<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/UL" class="company-name">联合利华 (Unilever)</a>的首席财务官表示，北美消费者在花掉疫情期间积累的超额积蓄时，“ <a href="https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://economics.cmail19.com/t/d-l-vykurjl-jitttilkij-q/__;!!F0Stn7g!DV3eXrYbx9JhECsWYg4fdcj9hFK4Boi0MRqviS41tozzX0mJOty4bazHM82zDFiVzUFJiz8ShIuC9w9fmOmO7AI$" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">开始表现出谨慎的迹象</a>”。</p><p> “我们仍然认为有可能出现温和的衰退，”首席财务官格雷姆·皮特凯斯利(Graeme Pitkethly)表示。</p><p>伊利诺伊州奥罗拉地区的 CertaPro Painters 总经理杰西·罗德里格斯 (Jesse Rodriguez) 表示，与一年前相比，客户对住宅油漆估价的请求减少了约 30%。</p><p>需求回落是在经历了两年的大流行中断之后发生的。 2021年，油漆公司招工速度不够快。去年，该公司因供应链混乱而陷入困境，限制了涂料的供应。</p><p> “我原本希望 23 年会是正常的一年，但事实证明并非如此，”罗德里格斯说。</p><p>罗德里格斯表示，随着业务放缓，该公司最近削减了营销费用，包括向潜在客户直邮传单的费用。</p><h3>长期前景乐观</h3><p>许多经济学家仍然预计经济增长将在今年晚些时候和 2024 年放缓，但他们<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/economists-are-cutting-back-their-recession-expectations-74118938?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">正在消除对经济衰退的担忧</a>。</p><p>世界大型企业联合会本周表示，7 月份美国消费者信心继续改善，许多美国人对未来表示更加乐观。消费者对经济衰退的担忧减少。</p><p>小企业对经济的感受也有所好转。商业辅导和同行咨询公司伟事达 (Vistage Worldwide) 的数据显示，7 月，37% 的小企业表示，他们认为未来 12 个月经济将恶化，这是自 2022 年 2 月以来的最佳记录。</p><p> <a href="https://www.imf.org/en/Publications/WEO/Issues/2023/07/10/world-economic-outlook-update-july-2023" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">国际货币基金组织周二表示</a>，今年美国和全球的经济增长可能会强于此前的估计。前景的改善反映了劳动力市场的强劲、旅游业等服务业支出的强劲以及金融稳定风险的降低。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> ——尼克·蒂米罗斯对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给 Sarah Chaney Cambon <a href="mailto:sarah.chaney@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">(sarah.chaney@wsj.com)</a>和 Christian Robles ( <a href="mailto:christian.robles@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">christian.robles@wsj.com</a> ) </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/newsroom-feedback/b53b02aa-8e94-4e61-9c59-71310c5dc08d.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 21:20:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-gdp-report-economic-growth-92482437</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-gdp-report-economic-growth-92482437<author><![CDATA[Sarah Chaney CambonChristian Robles]]></author><category>通货膨胀</category><category>gfx-contrib</category><category>银行业</category><category>中央银行业务</category><category>银行/信贷</category><category>金融服务</category><category>经济表现/指标</category><category>经济增长/衰退</category><category>消费者支出数据</category><category>货币政策</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>个人财务</category><category>消费者支出/预算</category><category>通货膨胀</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>瓦桑帕布</category><category>格雷姆·皮特凯斯利</category><category>艾米·克鲁斯·卡茨</category><category>杰罗姆·鲍威尔</category><category>格斯·阿亚拉</category><category>经济表现</category><category>指标</category><category>经济增长</category><category>经济衰退</category><category>消费者支出数字</category><category>货币政策</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>个人财务</category><category>消费支出</category><category>预算编制</category><category>银行业</category><category>中央银行</category><category>信用</category><category>金融服务</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[An Unwelcome Visitor Returns This Summer. Hint: It’s Covid.]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>又听说了一些新冠病例吗？这是有原因的<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824544/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>玛尔乔·沃尔特 (Margeaux Walter) 为《华尔街日报》<span>拍摄 玛尔乔·沃尔特 (Margeaux Walter) 为《华尔街日报》拍摄</span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001087824"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001087824"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sumathi-reddy"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-733259/AM" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sumathi-reddy" itemprop="url" rel="author">苏马蒂·雷迪</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">Updated July 27, 2023 4:21 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/covid-19-rates-rising-summer-780ab1d7"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>夏天给我们带来了炎热的日子、假期和新冠肺炎疫情。</p><p>如果您惊讶地发现您的邻居、同事或孩子最好的朋友刚刚检测出 Covid-19 呈阳性，请不要感到惊讶。根据美国疾病控制与预防中心的最新<a href="https://covid.cdc.gov/covid-data-tracker/?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email#maps_new-admissions-rate-county" target="_blank" class="icon none">数据</a>，全国范围内衡量新冠病毒感染率的指标，包括废水中的病毒水平、急诊室就诊次数、检测阳性率和住院人数，都在增加。好消息是我们的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-covid-19-deaths-and-hospitalizations-near-new-lows-9151bc18?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">利率非常低</a>。</p><p>医生们正在观察当前的趋势，寻找新冠病毒未来年度模式的线索。其他<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-does-flu-spread-compared-with-covid-what-to-know-as-flu-cases-surge-11667882271?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">呼吸道病毒，如流感</a>和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/fda-approves-first-rsv-drug-to-protect-all-infants-from-virus-52907caf?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">呼吸道合胞</a>病毒，通常在秋季开始传播，并在冬季达到高峰。新冠病毒是一种较新的病毒，自几年前出现以来已经发生了很大变异，到目前为止，它经历了冬季激增和夏季高峰，就像我们今年再次看到的那样。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>一个可能的因素是： <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sun-tired-hot-weather-heat-bb750670?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">热浪</a>导致人们逃往有空调的室内空间，与室外相比，新冠病毒在室内更容易传播。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/airport-travel-tips-flight-summer-a6771549?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">夏季旅行</a>也可能起到一定作用，因为人们涌入机场，并带着细菌在世界各地穿梭。</p><p> “我们正处于非常温暖的一年，人们在室内度过了很多时间，”传染病科主任路易斯·奥斯特罗斯基博士说<strong>&nbsp;</strong> UTHealth 休斯顿和纪念赫尔曼德克萨斯医学中心的流行病学。 “人们聚集在有空调的环境中，这为传播提供了机会。”</p><p>根据 CDC 数据，截至 7 月 15 日，Covid-19 住院人数较前一周增加 10.3%。急诊科就诊次数增加了 7%，检测阳性率从 5.8% 上升至 6.3%。入院人数包括因新冠肺炎住院的患者以及因其他原因入院治疗时检测呈阳性的患者。死亡人数仍然很低。</p><p>疾病预防控制中心发言人指出，总体而言，新冠感染率仍接近历史低点。对于大多数人来说，新冠病毒的危险性远没有以前那么严重了。</p><p> “因为我们可能会开始看到像对待其他呼吸道疾病那样的季节性模式，所以我认为今年夏天这波疫情的规模将非常明显，”疾病预防控制中心和白宫的科学顾问、《你的健康》一书的作者凯特琳·杰特琳娜 (Katelyn Jetelina) 说。当地流行病学家”时事通讯。</p><p>当前病例背后不存在新的冠状病毒菌株。科学家和医生表示， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-to-target-xbb-strain-when-covid-shots-roll-out-this-fall-178702e1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">XBB 变体</a>的混合体（Omicron 的分支）发挥着最大的作用。</p><p>杰特琳娜说，新冠病毒的变异速度比流感更快，因此它的变化速度更快，能够更好地逃避人们对先前感染的免疫力。</p><p>新冠病毒追踪数据不再像以前那么全面。许多人根本不进行检测，如果进行检测，也会使用<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/can-i-trust-my-rapid-covid-19-test-if-it-says-im-negative-11654650057?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">家庭快速检测</a>，但通常不会向卫生当局报告。</p><p>自联邦政府于 5 月份正式<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/covid-19-public-health-emergency-is-over-92ee814d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">宣布疫情结束</a>为突发公共卫生事件以来，实验室不再需要提交有关 Covid-19 检测的数据。相反，CDC 检测阳性数据来自 400 多个自愿提交数据的实验室。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824302?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">一家公司的数据显示，东北部废水中的病毒水平有所上升。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Matias Basualdo/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>废水检测提供了一些区域线索。 UTHealth Houston 和 Memorial Hermann 的 Ostrosky 表示，在休斯顿，废水处理措施在过去三周内增加了两倍。 “这始终是我们将在临床上看到的情况的先兆，”他指出。</p><p>奥斯特罗斯基说，过去两到三周内，医院和诊所的 Covid-19 检测呈阳性的人数大约增加了一倍。</p><p> The most recent data from Biobot, a Cambridge, Mass., wastewater epidemiology company, shows a 17% increase nationally in the level of the virus that causes Covid for the week ending July 26 compared with the prior week. “It&#39;s been this consistent uptick over the past several weeks,” says Mariana Matus, CEO and co-founder of Biobot.</p><p> The Midwest led the way with levels 40% higher for the week ending July 26 compared with the previous week. Levels were 13% higher in the Northeast and 15% higher in the South and Western states.</p><p>马图斯说，总体而言，废水病毒水平仍然很低。 Wastewater concentrations were three times higher last summer.</p><p>约翰霍普金斯大学健康安全中心的流行病学家凯特琳·里弗斯（Caitlin Rivers）表示，如果你年轻且健康，新冠趋势率并不一定需要改变行为。但如果感染人数继续上升一个月，老年人和免疫功能低下的人可能需要密切关注这些数字，并采取更加谨慎的行动，包括在拥挤的室内空间佩戴口罩。</p><p> “我们并没有陷入波浪深处，”里弗斯说。 “它只是朝着一个让我们更加关注的方向发展。”</p><p>写信给Sumathi Reddy： <a href="mailto:Sumathi.Reddy@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Sumathi.Reddy@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 20:21:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/covid-19-rates-rising-summer-780ab1d7</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/covid-19-rates-rising-summer-780ab1d7<author><![CDATA[Sumathi Reddy]]></author><category>摄影委托</category><category>WSJ生活工作</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>呼吸道疾病</category><category>健康</category><category>医疗条件</category><category>疫情/流行病</category><category>新型冠状病毒</category><category>传染性疾病</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>呼吸道疾病</category><category>健康</category><category>医疗条件</category><category>爆发</category><category>流行病</category><category>新型冠状病毒</category><category>传染性疾病</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Niger Coup Upends U.S. Security Plans in West Africa]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>多个国家的领导人被罢黜，这使得华盛顿打击基地组织和伊斯兰国变得更加困难<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001090648"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=DC3DD938-33C6-4ADA-887D-E8ED2882AEA7&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fniger-coup-upends-u-s-security-plans-in-west-africa-handing-russia-an-opportunity-8dcf6679&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Protesters in Niger looted and set fire to the headquarters of the ousted president&#39;s party on Thursday, after the country&#39;s army declared support to officers who took Mohamed Bazoum captive.照片：法新社/盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001090648"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/michael-m-phillips" itemprop="url" rel="author">Michael M. Phillips</a></span> 、 <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/benoit-faucon" itemprop="url" rel="author">Benoit Faucon</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/drew-hinshaw" itemprop="url" rel="author">Drew Hinshaw</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 27 日下午 3:43（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-upends-u-s-security-plans-in-west-africa-handing-russia-an-opportunity-8dcf6679"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>内罗毕——本周<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/apparent-coup-attempt-hits-u-s-ally-niger-e3efa36d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在尼日尔发生的军事政变</a>可能会扰乱美国打击伊斯兰激进分子的整个战略，因为伊斯兰激进分子在西非扩张，并可能在俄罗斯试图扩大自己在该地区的影响力时赋予其战略优势。</p><p>美国地区安全策略的核心是派遣美国突击队训练当地精锐部队<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-builds-new-firewall-to-stop-spread-of-militant-islamists-11670771719?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">对抗基地组织和伊斯兰国</a>，后者的暴力意识形态已从中东和南亚迅速蔓延到萨赫勒地区，萨赫勒地区是萨赫勒以南的半干旱地带。撒哈拉沙漠，过去六年。</p><p>现在，周三军官驱逐尼日尔总统穆罕默德·巴祖姆后的尘埃仍在尘埃落定中，美国发现自己受到美国法律的限制，该法律禁止其向军事政权提供大部分安全援助。尼日尔武装部队周四表示支持叛乱，华盛顿担心政变领导人在与美国分裂后可能会向武装分子割让更多阵地，转而求助于俄罗斯雇佣军来帮助他们反击。</p><p>巴祖姆于 2021 年当选，一直是美国竞选活动的基石盟友。这个幅员辽阔的西非国家拥有美国无人机和美国突击队，他们训练了尼日尔特种部队，并在打击博科圣地以及基地组织和伊斯兰国当地分支机构的战斗任务中为他们提供建议。 2017 年，四名美国士兵<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-military-recovers-body-of-fourth-soldier-killed-in-niger-ambush-1507319507?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在尼日尔的伊斯兰国伏击</a>中丧生。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="525" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824737?width=700&amp;height=525" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">尼日尔总统的支持者本周在一场军事政变中聚集在首都尼亚美。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>自2012年以来，美国已花费超过5亿美元来建设和训练武装部队。欧盟承诺向尼日尔提供10亿欧元的援助，这反过来又阻止了向北前往利比亚和地中海的移民潮。</p><p>过去两年<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/in-africa-u-s-trained-militaries-are-ousting-civilian-governments-in-coups-11649505601?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">布基纳法索和马里的政变</a>已经削弱了美国对该地区的军事援助；美国拨款法严格限制对推翻文官政府的军队的援助。尽管国务院律师尚未宣布尼日尔发生的事件为政变，但此举似乎有可能。</p><p>夺取政权后，马里和布基纳法索的军队从法国（西非大部分地区的前殖民国家）驱逐了军队。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-wagner-group-mercenaries-mali-west-africa-11661099199?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">马里雇佣了数百名与俄罗斯有联系的瓦格纳集团战士</a>，他们被指控屠杀平民并掠夺该国的自然资源。</p><p> “尼日尔是我们希望不会倒下的最后一张多米诺骨牌，”一位美国高级情报官员表示。 “如果它掉下来了，我不知道你会做什么。”这位官员表示，尼日尔是美国和法国军队在萨赫勒地区的“最后一个主要足迹”。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="882" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/b92d113d-bb08-4f8f-8bce-b2ab5d036186-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>美国指挥官担心政变会助长武装分子的气焰，特别是来自基地组织的武装分子。自 2017 年以来，该组织已在马里、尼日尔和布基纳法索发动了数千次袭击，目前正向南推进到科特迪瓦、多哥和贝宁的北部地区。美国和加纳官员担心，武装分子也将目光投向<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/al-qaeda-africa-ghana-u-s-ally-41a171fb?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">加纳。加纳是一个地区经济和政治强国，</a>在相对贫困的北部地区拥有大量穆斯林人口。</p><p> “尼日尔的政治不稳定仍然是一个主要问题，”贝宁的一名高级军官说。贝宁是一个沿海国家，其北部与受灾严重的布基纳法索和尼日尔接壤。 “从现在开始，我们可能会面临恐怖组织在我们共同边界上越来越多的活动。”</p><p>尽管美国官员周四对尼日尔政变可能会被扭转抱有模糊的希望，但实地证据表明巴祖姆的下台已经是最终决定。听取政变简报的前尼日尔和欧洲高级官员表示，军政府面临着军队中效忠派的有限反对，但现在占据了上风。</p><p>阿卜杜·西迪库·伊萨将军在周四发布的一份声明中表示，尼日尔武装部队高级军官决定支持叛乱，以“保护总统及其家人的人身安全，避免武装部队各部门之间发生血腥对抗”。军方发言人。</p><p>政变策划者的发言人阿马杜·阿卜杜拉马内少校周四在电视广播中表示，所有政党已被停职。他还指责法国在首都尼亚美机场降落一架军用飞机，违反了关闭该国领空的命令。尼日尔的许多外国军队，包括驻扎在那里的 1,100 名美国士兵中的一些，都驻扎在机场的军事一侧，称为 101 空军基地。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="394" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824739?width=700&amp;height=394" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">政变策划者的发言人阿马杜·阿卜杜拉马内少校在电视露面中发表了讲话。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：ORTN/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>美国高级情报官员表示，尼日尔军方可能仍希望与西方密切合作。但是，考虑到美国法律施加的限制，起义似乎可能会在华盛顿和尼日尔之间造成隔阂。</p><p> “这对美国来说是一个巨大的打击，”美国苏丹问题特使前幕僚长卡梅伦·哈德森说。 “我们为这位领导人提供了与该地区其他领导人不同的担保。”</p><p>去年在美国主导的华盛顿非洲领导人峰会上，拜登总统让巴祖姆坐在他旁边的荣誉座位上。国务卿安东尼·布林肯</p>3 月份访问尼日尔，宣布提供 1.5 亿美元的人道主义援助，美国外交官称此举是为了展示选择美国而不是瓦格纳的好处。<p></p><p>分析人士称，政变后与西方的决裂可能会给<a href="https://www.wsj.com/video/series/shelby-holliday/military-coups-in-africa-are-giving-russia-an-opening/9D3D941F-291D-4F85-B719-BD8A0CF4C8A0?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">莫斯科带来使用武器和雇佣军介入的机会</a>，就像它在马里所做的那样。</p><p> “尼日尔现在正在发挥作用，”现任华盛顿战略与国际研究中心高级研究员的哈德森说。 “它坚定地从西方阵营变成了俄罗斯机会主义的典范。”</p><p>俄罗斯外长拉夫罗夫表示，针对巴祖姆的政变是违宪的。 “在这种情况下，我们总是采取明确的立场，”他在该部网站上发表的评论中说。</p><p>双桅船。尼日尔特种部队指挥官、美军值得信赖的盟友穆萨·萨劳·巴尔穆将军是在首都尼亚美公开露面表示支持推翻政权的高级军官之一。巴尔穆将军没有回应置评请求。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824738?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">尼日尔总统穆罕默德·巴祖姆上个月在巴黎举行的一次聚会上。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：卢多维克·马林/新闻发布会</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>美国在几内亚、马里和布基纳法索训练的军队也向这些国家的文官政府发起攻击。</p><p>加纳阿克拉科菲·安南维和培训中心主任伊曼纽尔·奎西·阿宁教授表示：“美国的战略无助于萨赫勒地区，也无助于美国本身。”</p><p>官员们表示，这次起义是尼日尔自 1960 年脱离法国独立以来第五次此类政变，反映出军队内部多年来因未能击败伊斯兰叛乱分子而感到沮丧。军官们也对巴祖姆改革军队的尝试感到不安。 6 月，他的政府任命了自 2020 年起担任尼日尔武装部队总司令的萨利福·莫迪 (Salifou Modi) 为驻阿拉伯联合酋长国大使。周四，社交媒体用户猜测，无法联系到的莫迪现在将成为军政府领导人。</p><p>一位前欧洲官员表示，政变的另一个触发因素是巴祖姆决定减少总统卫队的财政福利，这支部队通过封锁总统官邸而带头起义。一年多来，总统一直在考虑是否解雇该部队指挥官奥马尔·奇亚尼将军。巴祖姆还一直在建立其他军事单位，以制衡总统卫队的权力。</p><p>随着巴祖姆官邸的对峙升级为政变企图，周三中午左右，巴祖姆接到了一名前美国官员的电话，该官员与美国外交和安全官员保持着定期联系。在那次通话中，巴祖姆向他的美国联系人保证，局势仍在控制之中，他预计军队很快就会到达他的住所并解除封锁。</p><p>相反，该国的高级将领站出来支持起义。 “这肯定会发生，”这位前欧洲官员谈到起义时说道。 “没有人感到惊讶。”</p><p>一年多来，美国和欧洲官员一直担心西非社交媒体网络上出现的虚假信息浪潮。在一个月前的视频中，一位法国新闻主播宣布尼日尔正在发生政变<span class="company-name-type">，</span>该视频在 TikTok 和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/META" class="">Facebook</a>上的观看次数超过一百万次；这些评论绝大多数是反法国的，指责总统是西方的傀儡。</p><p>其他病毒视频显示了恐怖袭击，试图证明美国在尼日尔的存在使该国变得不那么安全。去年，数千名尼日尔人在尼亚美街头游行，要求法国军队离开，其中一些人举着俄罗斯国旗或亲俄标语牌。</p><p> “俄罗斯不一定参与了政变本身，但为政变奠定了基础，这是非常明显的，”美国前驻非洲高级外交官 J. Peter Pham 表示。 “他们是否能够利用它，那是另一个问题了。”</p><p>白宫发言人表示，政府没有证据表明俄罗斯或瓦格纳集团是政变的幕后黑手。</p><p> — <em>Ann M. Simmons 对本文做出了贡献</em>。</p><p>写信给 Michael M. Phillips ( <a href="mailto:Michael.Phillips@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Michael.Phillips@wsj.com)</a> 、Benoit Faucon ( <a href="mailto:benoit.faucon@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">benoit.faucon@wsj.com</a> ) 和 Drew Hinshaw ( <a href="mailto:drew.hinshaw@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">drew.hinshaw@wsj.com</a> )</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 19:43:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https:/